Patches applied to vanilla vdr sources
-------------------------------------- 

vdr-2.6.3-dynamite.patch
    Lars Hanisch <dvb@flensrocker.de>, MarkusE (vdr-portal.de)

    Patch for VDR to support hotpluggable devices via the dynamite plugin.

04_newplugin.patch
    Thomas Schmidt <tschmidt@debian.org>

    Patch for the newplugin-script, to not require a normal vdr-source-dir

81_Make_config.patch
    Tobias Grimm <vdr@e-tobi.net>

    Add Make.config to compile debug versions.

99_ncursesw-include.patch
    Tobias Grimm <tg@e-tobi.net>

    Use ncursesw header file

opt-37-x_menuorg.patch
    Tobias Grimm <tg@e-tobi.net>

    This patch is required by the MenuOrg plugin. It adds a service interface,
    that can be implemented by plugins to reorganize  VDR's main menu entries
    with the ability to create custom sub menus. This is version 0.5.s of the
    patch

opt-42-x_MainMenuHooks-v1.0.1.patch
    Frank Schmirler <vdrdev@schmirler.de>

    This patch allows plugins to replace the VDR mainmenus "Schedule",
    "Channels", "Timers" and "Recordings" by a different implementation.

opt-56_eventdetails_v3.patch
    Michael Eiler <eiler.mike@gmail.com>      

    Patch for vdr-plugin-restfulapi

opt-65_pin.patch
    Jörg Wendel (horchi@vdr-portal)

    patch for the pin plugin

vdr-2.3.9-hide-first-recording-level-v2.patch
    Lars Hanisch <dvb@flensrocker.de>, Saman (vdr-portal.de)

    Hide the first level of directories in the recordings menu, all recordings
    are stored at the "local" directory

vdr-2.2.0-missing-plugin.patch
    Ville Skyttä <ville.skytta@iki.fi>

    Don't exit with an error if a plugin can't be loaded

vdr-2.4.2_undelete.diff
    kamel5

    this patch allows to restore deleted recordings until the vdr scrubs them
    from disk

vdr-2.6-patch-for-permashift.diff
    Eike Sauer <eike.sauer@web.de>

    Add permashift functionality to vdr

fix-StopSectionHandler.patch
    Markus Ehrnsperger

    delete sectionHandler first to prevent use with partially deleted
    dependencies

